  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Operations Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview / Employee Value Proposition</strong></p><p>At GoldenHome (S) Pte Ltd, we strive to exceed client expectations through our dedication to quality, sustainability, and innovative design. Our mission is to provide tailored carpentry services that not only meet but surpass industry standards, building long lasting relationships with our clients and partners.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Coordinate and manage carpentry projects and back-office operations to deliver high-quality, compliant solutions. Collaborate with stakeholders to drive process improvements and foster strong customer and partner relationships.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate back-office support activities to ensure timely and accurate processing of retail and project orders</li><li>Assist in preparing tenders, developing cost estimates, and planning supply requirements to support project execution</li><li>Manage carpentry projects by overseeing materials procurement, quality control, and adherence to project timelines</li><li>Collaborate effectively with developers, contractors, architects, and clients to align project objectives and deliverables</li><li>Ensure all carpentry work complies with relevant building codes and safety standards to maintain regulatory compliance</li><li>Conduct product training sessions and provide ongoing technical support to internal teams and clients</li><li>Analyze and improve operational and office processes to enhance efficiency and service delivery</li><li>Identify, troubleshoot, and resolve project and carpentry-related issues to minimize delays and maintain quality</li><li>Build and maintain strong relationships with customers and partners to support business growth and repeat engagements</li><li>Perform additional duties as assigned to support organizational goals and project success</li></ul>",
